It’s understood the man was attacked on Friday night after he left his tractor, which stalled a few metres before he could reach his compound. JOHANNESBURG - Police in Limpopo are investigating after a 46-year-old man was attacked and killed by lions at a game farm near Hoedspruit. It’s understood the man was attacked on Friday night after he left his tractor, which stalled a few metres before he could reach his compound. Police say the man's body was recovered after the lions were scared off by gunshots. The police's Moatshe Ngope says: “He walked on foot and subsequently a group of lions attacked him. At this stage, our investigations continue.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)